Plug-in name: Studia
Plug-in shortname: studia
Description: Tools for Eva case studies

Most options of the form '-studia-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-studia-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:


*** DEBUG

-studia-debug <n>   level of debug for plug-in Studia (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-studia-help        help of plug-in Studia
-studia-h           alias for option -studia-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-studia-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Studia to a file. <K> is
                    a combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -studia-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-studia-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -studia-msg-key help to get a list of
                    available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -studia-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-studia-verbose <n>  level of verbosity for plug-in Studia (default to 1)
-studia-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category
                    <k1> to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -studia-warn-key help
                    to get a list of available categories, and * to enable
                    all categories. Possible statuses are inactive, feedback,
                    warning, error, abort, feedback-once, warning-once,
                    error-once. Defaults to warning. (preferably use
                    -studia-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
